        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 11:13AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1113 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Farnsworth, or 8 miles southwest of Perryton, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wolf Creek Park and Farnsworth.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
